[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] Technique of approximating ambient occlusion in screen space.
[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] ; it is typically rendered onto other geometry in the main rendering pass.
[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] One of the techniques of adding shadows to 3D scenes.
[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] Method of creating background for a 3D scene by enclosing it in a textured cuboid (or another environment map).
[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] A texture that can partially reside in the video memory to reduce video memory usage and loading time.
[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] These highlights depend on the viewer's position as well as the position of the light source and surface normal.
[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] 2D image moving on the screen, with potential partial transparency and/or animation.
[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] A buffer storing an integer value for each according screen pixel, used e.g. to mask out specific operations and achieve specific effects.
[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] surface, typically compared with the light and view vectors to compute the resulting visible colour.
[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] Converting a general 3D surface into polygonal representation, important because of HW being optimized for rendering polygons.
[src:decal-rendering/g-buffer] reads, accelerating texture sampling operations.
